modules.description: Implements path-based routing using string literals to define routes, mapping them to handlers. Works with route lists and dispatch tables, enabling concrete use cases like REST API endpoint handling or client-side fragment navigation. Directly translates route patterns into executable dispatch logic.

This module implements path-based routing for mapping hierarchical paths to handlers, using literal and variable path segments with exact or prefix matching. It supports constructing route tables, dispatching paths, and extracting variables during traversal, enabling use cases like REST API routing on servers or fragment-based navigation in clients. The child module provides a concrete interface for defining routes with string literals, translating them into executable dispatch logic that maps directly to handler functions. Together, they enable efficient, structured routing with both static and dynamic path components.
